<font face="verdana"> 

<div> 

 
 Workforce1 is recruiting qualified individuals for Forever 21 Store opening--Hiring 200+ employees. 
<div> <br>

<b>Store Associates:</b> 
<ul><li> Responsible for assisting in the daily operations of the store. Must be able to work in the areas of merchandise presentation, processing, markdowns, fitting room, cashier, customer service and layaway. Greets, interacts with and thanks customers on a regular basis. Maintains housekeeping standards of area, including ongoing recovery. Performs other duties, as assigned. Part-time or full-time. 
 </ul>

<ul><li> 
 Candidate must have experience as a Cashier.  Strong Mathematical Skills.  Customer Service Skills are a must.
 </ul>
<b>Requirements:</b>
<ul><li> Willingness to work as part of a team, Good verbal skills, Energetic and enthusiastic, Professional appearance, 
Ability to stand for extended periods of time, Capacity for lifting up to 50 lbs, reaching overhead, bending, twisting
<li> Ability to work flexible, full-time schedule to include days, evenings, weekends and holidays.</ul>

<b>In order to apply and be considered for these positions, interested candidates must attend a screening interview conducted by Workforce1 at a recruitment event below.</b><br><br>
<b>Date:</b> Friday, March 17, 2017<br><br>
<b>Check in:</b> 9:00 AM to 9:15 AM (No admittance after 9:15 AM) <br><br>
OR <br> <br>
<b>Check in:</b> 12:00 PM to 12:15 PM (No admittance after 12:15 PM) <br><br>
<b>Location:</b> 400 East Fordham Road, 8th Floor, Bronx NY 10458<br><br>

Please come with a valid photo ID, 2 copies of your resume and a pen. Professional attire is required. <br> <br>
<b> *** Please ask for Eva upon arrival *** </b> <hr>
<img src="http://www.nyc.gov/html/sbs/wf1/images/branding/wf1_logo_web.jpg" height="45">
<p><b><a href="http://www.nyc.gov/workforce1" rel="nofollow">Workforce1</a></b> is a service that attracts, prepares, and connects qualified candidates to job opportunities in New York City. We use a combination of recruitment expertise, industry knowledge, and services that strengthen candidates' employment prospects to make strong matches for job candidates and businesses alike.
<br><br>To learn more, visit <a href="http://www.nyc.gov/wf1recruitment" rel="nofollow">nyc.gov/wf1recruitment</a>. Don't forget to <a href="http://www.facebook.com/nycworkforce1" rel="nofollow">like us on Facebook</a>, follow <a href="http://twitter.com/nycworkforce1" rel="nofollow">@NYCWorkforce1</a>, and visit our <a href="http://nycworkforce1.org" rel="nofollow">Career Blog</a>.
<br><br> Equal opportunity employer/program. Auxiliary aids and services are available upon request to individuals with disabilities.
</p></div>
